Shen Yun Performing Arts performed in seven cities in France, South Korea, and the United States during the week of February 17-23, 2020, including four sold-out shows at the Cité des Congrès de Nantes in Nantes, France, February 21–23, 2020; four sold-out shows at the Palais des Congrès de Tours, in Tours, France, February 18–20; and two sold-out shows at the Ordway Center for the Performing Arts in Saint Paul, Minnesota, on February 22, 2020.


The Shen Yun Touring Company presented four sold-out shows at the Cité des Congrès de Nantes in Nantes, France, February 21–23.


The Shen Yun Touring Company also presented four sold-out shows at the Palais des Congrès de Tours, in Tours, France, February 18–20.


Shen Yun World Company presented two sold-out shows at the Ordway Center for the Performing Arts in Saint Paul, Minnesota, on February 22.


Mayor of Saint Paul, Melvin Carter, proclaims “Celebrating Shen Yun Day.”

The mayor of Saint Paul, Melvin Carter, proclaimed February 20, “Celebrating Shen Yun Day.”

“Comes from the Heart”

Sarwat Kaluby, a dance judge, studio owner, and former ballerino, saw Shen Yun at the Thrasher-Horne Center in Jacksonville, Florida, on February 22, 2020.

Classically trained in ballet, Florida-based Sarwat Kaluby earned his BA and MA in choreography at the Kirov (Mariinsky) Theatre in St. Petersburg and has danced with renowned companies such as the New York City Ballet and the Paris Opera House. He saw Shen Yun's performance at the Thrasher-Horne Center in Jacksonville, Florida, on February 22.
